                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/39109",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jcsanyi",
                        "name": "jcsanyi",
                        "displayName": "Jonathan Csanyi",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "'sorry.. original diff had a misleading\/incorrect comment.\r\nThis is the correct diff.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jcsanyi",
                        "name": "jcsanyi",
                        "displayName": "Jonathan Csanyi",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-03-08T18:00:28.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-03-08T18:00:28.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/41482",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=cduv",
                        "name": "cduv",
                        "displayName": "Claude Duvergier",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I agree with _Jonathan Csanyi_.\r\n\r\nI ran into that problem an thought {{Zend_Rest_Client}} was the cause as it uses the \"arg1\" query parameter name when only one argument is passed to the server (see ZF-4910).\r\nBut is seems that {{Zend_Rest_Server}} is guilty.\r\n\r\nWith the following server PHP code:\r\n{code:title=ServerCode}\r\nclass MyServerImpl\r\n{\r\n  public function myMethod ($var)\r\n  {\r\n    $return $var*$var;\r\n  }\r\n  public function myOtherMethod ($var = 3)\r\n  {\r\n    $return $var*$var;\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n$server = new Zend_Rest_Server();\r\n$server->setClass('MyServerImpl');\r\n$server->handle();\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nThe following client PHP code:\r\n{code:title=ClientCode1}\r\n$client\r\n  ->myMethod(5)\r\n  ->get();\r\n{code}\r\nIssues the following request:\r\n{{server.php?method=*myMethod*&*myMethod*=5&arg1=*5*}}\r\n\r\nWhich is handled by {{Zend_Rest_Server::handle()}} as \r\n{code:title=HandlingClientCode1}\r\n$missing_args[0] = 'var';\r\n$calling_args[1] = 5\r\n=> myMethod(5);\r\n{code}\r\n{color:green}Which is correct.{color}\r\n\r\nAnd the other following client PHP code:\r\n{code:title=ClientCode2}\r\n$client\r\n  ->myOtherMethod(5)\r\n  ->get();\r\n{code}\r\nIssues the following request:\r\n{{server.php?method=*myOtherMethod*&*myOtherMethod*=5&arg1=*5*}}\r\n\r\nWhich is handled by {{Zend_Rest_Server::handle()}} as \r\n{code:title=HandlingClientCode2}\r\n$missing_args[] = array();\r\n$calling_args[0] = 3;\r\n$calling_args[1] = 5;\r\n=> myOtherMethod(3);\r\n{code}\r\n{color:red}Which is incorrect.{color}\r\n\r\nThe solution would be to either use 0-based array everywhere, or the given \"library\/Zend\/Rest\/Server.php\" DIFF file [^trunk-correct.diff].",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=cduv",
                        "name": "cduv",
                        "displayName": "Claude Duvergier",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-07-15T03:23:47.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-07-15T03:23:47.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
